Heat oven to 375 degrees F. In large bowl combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup ketchup. Mix well, using hands if necessary. Divide mixture evenly into two 8x4- or 9x5-inch loaf pans. Spread 1/4 cup ketchup on top of each meatloaf. Bake 70 to 75 minutes or until center of meatloaf reaches 160 degrees F. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.